{
  "$comment": "Neutral shipped <windows.h> (Win32) SKELETON — c95 (the FLIP-AND-UNBLOCK cycle of the Windows-host sub-arc). Predefining `_WIN32` (pe-gated, c-subset.lang.json) makes sqlite's amalgamation select its OWN os_win.c VFS (SQLITE_OS_WIN) instead of os_unix. os_win.c then needs the Win32 TYPE + STRUCT + CONSTANT vocabulary to PARSE; this descriptor supplies exactly that surface (the 13 core types + the 6 field-bearing records os_win.c reads members of + the constants it references). `availableObjectFormats:[pe]` — a Win32 header is meaningless on elf/macho (a reference there fails loud). `library:{pe:kernel32.dll}` — the eventual kernel32 import library (pe already imports kernel32 for ExitProcess). ★ SCOPE (c95): enough that os_win.c PARSES. The kernel32 FUNCTION declarations (the aSyscall[] table) were DEFERRED to c96+ and are shipped incrementally in the `symbols` block: ★ c101 (2026-07-04) shipped the SYNC slice — the `structs` SRWLOCK (8B) + CRITICAL_SECTION (RTL_CRITICAL_SECTION, 40B on x64) + 9 mutex fns (Initialize/Delete/Enter/Leave/TryEnter*CriticalSection + Initialize/Acquire/Release/TryAcquire*SRWLockExclusive), all real kernel32 exports (NTDLL forwarders). The file/heap/time kernel32 batch (~40 fns: CreateFileW/ReadFile/WriteFile/LockFileEx/GetSystemTimeAsFileTime/Heap*/MapViewOfFile/…) is c102. ★ NOTE: `InterlockedCompareExchange` (sqlite's winMutex atomic) is an x64 INTRINSIC (`lock cmpxchg`), NOT a kernel32 export — deliberately NOT shipped here: DSS EAGER-IMPORTS a descriptor's symbols for ANY program that `#include`s it, so a non-export symbol in `symbols` breaks the pe loader of every such program (STATUS_ENTRYPOINT_NOT_FOUND 0xC0000139 — it broke the windows_predefine_macro example). Deferred to the c103 intrinsic-builtin cycle (with `__umulh`). TYPE MAPPINGS: HANDLE/LPVOID/LPCVOID/HMODULE/HLOCAL/FARPROC and the LP*_ pointer types → ptr<void> (Win32 opaque handles + C pointer coercion); LPCSTR/LPSTR → ptr<char> (ANSI); LPCWSTR/LPWSTR → ptr<u16> (UTF-16, WCHAR=u16); DWORD/UINT/ULONG → u32; LONG/BOOL/INT → i32; SIZE_T/ULONGLONG → u64; WCHAR → u16; VOID → void (the `(VOID)` empty prototype). GET_FILEEX_INFO_LEVELS is an enum → i32. LLP64 note: Win32 `LONG` is 32-bit (i32) even on 64-bit Windows (unlike POSIX `long`); the 64-bit forms use ULONGLONG/LARGE_INTEGER, so no `long`-width axis is needed here. STRUCT LAYOUTS (natural C alignment, the layout engine derives offsets from field sizes — matching the real windows.h records os_win reads): OVERLAPPED flattens its anonymous Offset/OffsetHigh union-struct (os_win writes .Offset/.OffsetHigh/.hEvent) → 32B; LARGE_INTEGER is modeled as a struct {i64 QuadPart} (os_win only ever touches .QuadPart, the widest 8B union member — a true `union` needs a descriptor `unions` block, out of c95 scope) → 8B; SYSTEM_INFO carries the real field order so .dwPageSize@4 / .dwAllocationGranularity@40 land correctly; FILETIME {u32,u32}=8B; WIN32_FILE_ATTRIBUTE_DATA {dwFileAttributes, 3×FILETIME, nFileSizeHigh, nFileSizeLow}=36B (os_win reads .dwFileAttributes/.nFileSizeHigh/.nFileSizeLow). Each record is ALSO a bare typedef (os_win declares `OVERLAPPED ovlp;` without the `struct` keyword) whose inline `struct \"Name\"{…}` interns to the SAME TypeId as the structs-block entry (name + field-types identity), so the injected field scope resolves .member. CONSTANT values verified against the Windows SDK headers (winnt.h/winbase.h/fileapi.h/handleapi.h/memoryapi.h/errhandlingapi.h/winerror.h).",
